Iron-Ore Swaps Trading Jumped 50% in August, Steel Index Reports

-- B y   A l a r i c   N i g h t i n g a l e
-- 
2011-09-05T09:21:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-05/iron-ore-swaps-trading-jumped-50-in-august-steel-index-reports.html
Trading in iron-ore swaps climbed 50
percent to a record in August, The Steel Index reported.  Investors bought and sold derivatives corresponding to more
than 6.5 million metric tons of the steelmaking raw material, up
from 4.3 million tons in July, the provider of steel prices said
in an e-mailed report today. The combined nominal value of
trading was $1.1 billion, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alaric Nightingale in London at 
 anightingal1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stuart Wallace at   swallace6@bloomberg.net  